    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-12-28T18:57:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-12-28T18:57:00-05:00" n="1415"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1415">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">851G.131/12–2854: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in France</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d1415fn1">Drafted by <persName>Tyson</persName> of <gloss
                            target="#t_PSA1">PSA</gloss>. Repeated to Saigon for information as
                        telegram 2624.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-12-28T18:57:00-05:00"
                            >December 28, 1954—6:57 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2342. Department’s 1974 repeated Saigon 2171.<note n="2" xml:id="d1415fn2">The
                        reference telegram, dated Nov. 29, not printed, indicated that the
                        Vietnamese Ambassador had inquired whether the United States would be
                        willing to advance $100 million to the State of Vietnam during January 1955.
                        (851G.131/11–2954)</note>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Viet Ambassador called obtain reply inquiry re $100 million advance
                        mentioned reference telegram. Department read and gave him copy following
                        statement which was prepared by <gloss target="#t_FOAW1">FOA/W</gloss>:
                            <quote rend="blockquote">
                            <p>“In view of Congressional requirements under our <gloss
                                    target="#t_MSP1">MSP</gloss> legislation and our policies in
                                respect to foreign aid programs, we cannot make lump sum advances of
                                aid funds in the manner requested by the Vietnamese Ambassador.
                                However, our Mission in Saigon has under study in consultation with
                                the Vietnamese Government means by which piasters could be generated
                                during the early part of next year for purposes provided for in the
                                U.S. aid program—within the limit of available U.S. funds for these
                                purposes. In this connection we are particularly <pb facs="1051"
                                    n="2433" xml:id="pg_2433"/> concerned that more flexible piaster
                                funding arrangements be made through the establishment of the new
                                central bank now contemplated in Saigon. We are also contemplating
                                the maximum possible liberalization of our regulations relating to
                                the purchase of imports for Viet Nam under regular <gloss
                                    target="#t_FOA1">FOA</gloss> procedures.</p>
                            <p>“We are confident that arrangements will be worked out to assure
                                sufficient availability of piasters to the Government of Viet Nam to
                                carry on necessary governmental operations during the transition
                                period following the inauguration of direct aid.”</p>
                        </quote>
                    </item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Ambassador stated request originated by <persName>Thoai</persName>
                        <note n="3" xml:id="d1415fn3">
                            <persName>Nguyen Van Thoai</persName>, Vietnamese Secretary of State for
                            Economic Affairs.</note> in Paris and asked if US Embassy Paris could
                        pass statement given above to <persName>Thoai</persName>. Unless objection
                        perceived request Embassy do so.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
